    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for bash.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The bash packages provide Bash (Bourne-again shell), which is the default shell for Rocky Linux.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* bash: a heap-buffer-overflow in valid_parameter_transform (CVE-2022-3715)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
